- toFixed(2)is used for setting how many decimal points you want.

document.querySelector() is for first element. and .querySelectorAll() is for all elements

lets say fruits

for class is querySelectorAll(".fruits)
for id is querySelectorAll("#fruits")
for tag is querySelectorAll("div")

Array.from(".fruits).forEach(fruit => {
    fruit.style.backgroundColor = yellow;
})


-  eventListener("event type eg click", function or callback)
event.target.textContent, target is used to target the id that is using the eventListener